verbose_text: At the end of reperfusion, the cardiac function indexes, serum lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) and creatine kinase (CK) levels, heart weight (HW)/body weight (BW) ratio and infarct size, and expressions of phosphatidylinositol-3 kinase / serine-threonine protein kinase (PI3K / AKT) and glycogen synthase kinase-3beta (GSK-3beta) proteins and the phosphorylated forms (p-AKT, p-GSK-3beta) were determined.
